      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RED HOT PRETTY (2) turned in a modest effort most recently when eighth at Healesville over 350m behind Ridiculous (19.94) in a Grade 5. Was in the money prior to that. Has performed well from this box with a win and two minor placings to her name from five starts. Has claims if she runs up to expectations. BUSTER BOURBSKI (1) doesn't win out of turn but looks close to breaking through. Has hit the frame the last two runs, the latest when third (17.16) at Healesville. Expecting another good run. JAICOS (4) held his own to the line last start and filled a minor placing, beaten only 2 lengths (24.48) behind Paw Brody at Bendigo. Some good form is emerging from his last run. Overdue and is among the main hopes. GREMLIN (7) will need to run right up to last start to feature again.",
